OL,5,Cbombings
OL,7,F"And whilst the rawness of the wounds
OL,8,Fof the families and regiments who
OL,9,Fsuffered almost unimaginable loss that
OL,10,Fnight may have dulled a little over
OL,11,Fthe years, the depth of their loss is
OL,12,Fincalculable.
OL,14,F"We may be thankful for the Good
OL,15,FFriday Agreement, and that the
OL,16,Findiscriminate bombing of our towns
OL,17,Fand cities by Irish paramilitaries has
OL,18,Flong ceased, but crimes unsolved and
OL,19,Fperpetrators unpunished still leave so
OL,20,Fmuch up in the air, with closure hard
OL,21,Fto come by."
